== Potatoes ==

Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Put a large #saucepan{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} on to boil.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm chunks (peel first if you prefer).

When boiling, add the potatoes to the water and cook until you can easily slip a knife through, ~{15-18%minutes}.

== Prep ==

Meanwhile, roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1%bunch}(chopped, stalks and all).

Trim the @green beans{80%grams}.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Zest and halve the @lemon{1/2}.

== Basa ==

Lay the @basa fillets{2} on a lined #baking tray{} and sprinkle over half the @cajun spice mix{1%sachet}.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and drizzle with @olive oil{1.5%tbsp}, then rub the flavourings into the fish.

Bake the basa on the middle shelf until cooked, ~{10-12%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish. It's cooked when opaque in the middle.

== Parsley Dressing ==

Meanwhile, put the remaining Cajun spice mix into a small #bowl{}.

Add the lemon zest, then squeeze in some lemon juice.

Season with salt, then mix in the olive oil for the dressing and half the parsley.

Add more lemon juice to taste.

== Green Beans and Broccoli ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Halve any thick broccoli stems lengthways.

Once hot, add the green beans and @tenderstem® broccoli{80%grams} to the pan. Stir-fry for ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Add a splash of water, then cover with a #lid{} and allow to cook until the veg is tender, ~{2-3%minutes}.

== Mash ==

Once the potatoes are cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the saucepan, off the heat.

Add a splash of @?milk{some} and a knob of @?butter{some}(if you have any) and mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth.

Stir through the remaining parsley, then season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Share the mash between your #bowls{}, then top with the green beans, broccoli and basa.

Finish by drizzling over the spicy parsley dressing. Enjoy!